{"id": "1971020465427857803", "kind": "tweet", "username": "euxenus", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:33+00:00", "text": "I argue that using higher values of beta like 4 will decrease entropy a bit and stabilize training.\n\nTop is F, bottom is entropy.\n\nIf a linear or MLP head (instead of their Q/K routing) will ever work it's probably going to need some kind of entropy regularization like this https://t.co/RAORyn9sq3", "url": "https://x.com/euxenus/status/1971020465427857803", "favorite_count": 5, "retweet_count": 0, "source_dataset": "supabase_incremental", "api_fetched_at": "2026-06-29T18:42:12.114188+00:00", "raw": {"tweet_id": "1971020465427857803", "account_id": "1166420252898603008", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:33+00:00", "full_text": "I argue that using higher values of beta like 4 will decrease entropy a bit and stabilize training.\n\nTop is F, bottom is entropy.\n\nIf a linear or MLP head (instead of their Q/K routing) will ever work it's probably going to need some kind of entropy regularization like this https://t.co/RAORyn9sq3", "retweet_count": 0, "favorite_count": 5, "reply_to_tweet_id": "1971020462223393040", "reply_to_user_id": null, "reply_to_username": null, "archive_upload_id": null, "fts": "'/raoryn9sq3':54 '4':10 'argu':2 'beta':8 'bit':15 'bottom':22 'decreas':12 'entropi':13,24,48 'ever':37 'f':21 'go':42 'head':30 'higher':5 'instead':31 'kind':46 'like':9,50 'linear':27 'mlp':29 'need':44 'probabl':41 'q/k':34 'regular':49 'rout':35 'stabil':17 't.co':53 't.co/raoryn9sq3':52 'top':19 'train':18 'use':4 'valu':6 'work':38", "updated_at": "2026-06-29T04:03:30.414194+00:00"}}
{"id": "1971020468338688300", "kind": "tweet", "username": "euxenus", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:34+00:00", "text": "Directly penalizing high entropy via a regularization term also works, I find. Binary entropy itself has unsuitable  gradients imo so I propose an alternative: the square of distance to the nearest boundary (0 or 1). https://t.co/9WXIBTjdpT", "url": "https://x.com/euxenus/status/1971020468338688300", "favorite_count": 5, "retweet_count": 0, "source_dataset": "supabase_incremental", "api_fetched_at": "2026-06-29T18:42:12.114188+00:00", "raw": {"tweet_id": "1971020468338688300", "account_id": "1166420252898603008", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:34+00:00", "full_text": "Directly penalizing high entropy via a regularization term also works, I find. Binary entropy itself has unsuitable  gradients imo so I propose an alternative: the square of distance to the nearest boundary (0 or 1). https://t.co/9WXIBTjdpT", "retweet_count": 0, "favorite_count": 5, "reply_to_tweet_id": "1971020465427857803", "reply_to_user_id": null, "reply_to_username": null, "archive_upload_id": null, "fts": "'/9wxibtjdpt':38 '0':33 '1':35 'also':9 'altern':24 'binari':13 'boundari':32 'direct':1 'distanc':28 'entropi':4,14 'find':12 'gradient':18 'high':3 'imo':19 'nearest':31 'penal':2 'propos':22 'regular':7 'squar':26 't.co':37 't.co/9wxibtjdpt':36 'term':8 'unsuit':17 'via':5 'work':10", "updated_at": "2026-06-29T04:03:30.414194+00:00"}}
{"id": "1971020471266414942", "kind": "tweet", "username": "euxenus", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:34+00:00", "text": "I analyze the \"confidence STE\" and note that it doesn't obviously decrease entropy in itself. That the official checkpoints have low entropy has to be an emergent property after a lot of training steps.\n\nI note that the conf STE is weird and propose some similar alternatives https://t.co/v8JcRNRpw8", "url": "https://x.com/euxenus/status/1971020471266414942", "favorite_count": 5, "retweet_count": 1, "source_dataset": "supabase_incremental", "api_fetched_at": "2026-06-29T18:42:12.114188+00:00", "raw": {"tweet_id": "1971020471266414942", "account_id": "1166420252898603008", "created_at": "2025-09-25T01:14:34+00:00", "full_text": "I analyze the \"confidence STE\" and note that it doesn't obviously decrease entropy in itself. That the official checkpoints have low entropy has to be an emergent property after a lot of training steps.\n\nI note that the conf STE is weird and propose some similar alternatives https://t.co/v8JcRNRpw8", "retweet_count": 1, "favorite_count": 5, "reply_to_tweet_id": "1971020468338688300", "reply_to_user_id": null, "reply_to_username": null, "archive_upload_id": null, "fts": "'/v8jcrnrpw8':51 'altern':48 'analyz':2 'checkpoint':20 'conf':40 'confid':4 'decreas':13 'doesn':10 'emerg':28 'entropi':14,23 'lot':32 'low':22 'note':7,37 'obvious':12 'offici':19 'properti':29 'propos':45 'similar':47 'ste':5,41 'step':35 't.co':50 't.co/v8jcrnrpw8':49 'train':34 'weird':43", "updated_at": "2026-06-29T04:03:30.414194+00:00"}}
