{"id": "1971046935403565387", "kind": "tweet", "username": "euxenus", "created_at": "2025-09-25T02:59:44+00:00", "text": "@main_horse yes good question. that period is longer with larger beta.  for 4 it pops out of that phase in 50 steps, for 8 it takes 100 steps.\n\nI think it's just because on init the ps are around 0.5, they immediately get pushed down low, then it takes a bit to recover", "url": "https://x.com/euxenus/status/1971046935403565387", "favorite_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0, "source_dataset": "supabase_incremental", "api_fetched_at": "2026-06-29T18:42:12.114188+00:00", "raw": {"tweet_id": "1971046935403565387", "account_id": "1166420252898603008", "created_at": "2025-09-25T02:59:44+00:00", "full_text": "@main_horse yes good question. that period is longer with larger beta.  for 4 it pops out of that phase in 50 steps, for 8 it takes 100 steps.\n\nI think it's just because on init the ps are around 0.5, they immediately get pushed down low, then it takes a bit to recover", "retweet_count": 0, "favorite_count": 0, "reply_to_tweet_id": "1971037018282131700", "reply_to_user_id": null, "reply_to_username": null, "archive_upload_id": null, "fts": "'0.5':42 '100':28 '4':14 '50':22 '8':25 'around':41 'beta':12 'bit':53 'get':45 'good':4 'hors':2 'immedi':44 'init':37 'larger':11 'longer':9 'low':48 'main':1 'period':7 'phase':20 'pop':16 'ps':39 'push':46 'question':5 'recov':55 'step':23,29 'take':27,51 'think':31 'yes':3", "updated_at": "2026-06-29T04:03:30.414194+00:00"}}
{"id": "1971047412421755025", "kind": "tweet", "username": "euxenus", "created_at": "2025-09-25T03:01:38+00:00", "text": "@main_horse the gradient of softstep drops off as a polynomial in beta near the boundaries.\n\nidt this early training phase is a real problem but you could just do something like\n\n(F_4 + F_1)(F-q)\n\nwould probably fix by making sure there is more gradient pressure near 0 and 1 https://t.co/j41oa5txHK", "url": "https://x.com/euxenus/status/1971047412421755025", "favorite_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0, "source_dataset": "supabase_incremental", "api_fetched_at": "2026-06-29T18:42:12.114188+00:00", "raw": {"tweet_id": "1971047412421755025", "account_id": "1166420252898603008", "created_at": "2025-09-25T03:01:38+00:00", "full_text": "@main_horse the gradient of softstep drops off as a polynomial in beta near the boundaries.\n\nidt this early training phase is a real problem but you could just do something like\n\n(F_4 + F_1)(F-q)\n\nwould probably fix by making sure there is more gradient pressure near 0 and 1 https://t.co/j41oa5txHK", "retweet_count": 0, "favorite_count": 0, "reply_to_tweet_id": "1971046935403565387", "reply_to_user_id": null, "reply_to_username": null, "archive_upload_id": null, "fts": "'/j41oa5txhk':57 '0':52 '1':36,54 '4':34 'beta':13 'boundari':16 'could':28 'drop':7 'earli':19 'f':33,35,38 'f-q':37 'fix':42 'gradient':4,49 'hors':2 'idt':17 'like':32 'main':1 'make':44 'near':14,51 'phase':21 'polynomi':11 'pressur':50 'probabl':41 'problem':25 'q':39 'real':24 'softstep':6 'someth':31 'sure':45 't.co':56 't.co/j41oa5txhk':55 'train':20 'would':40", "updated_at": "2026-06-29T04:03:30.414194+00:00"}}
